<br> "Now I want to tell my story with my words," explained Pelicot in the press release, with the same courage shown during the long trial against the husband and about fifty men he sold it, after drugging it, and who raped him while he was unconscious.
"Through this book I hope to convey a message of strength and courage to all those who are facing terrible trials," he continued, "who are never ashamed. And that, with time, they learn to enjoy life again and find peace," explains Pelicot in the press.&nbsp;
